# ğŸŒ Node.js REST API

A simple RESTful API built with **Express.js**, **CORS**, and **MongoDB**, designed for testing HTTP requests and network access.  
This backend can be accessed from **any device on the same local network** and is ready for integration with frontend apps (React, Vue, etc.).

---

## ğŸš€ Features

- âš™ï¸ Built with [Express](https://expressjs.com/)
- ğŸŒ CORS enabled (open access for all origins)
- ğŸ’¾ MongoDB integration (local or remote)
- ğŸ§© Follows MVC project structure
- ğŸ§  JSON request/response support
- ğŸ–¼ï¸ Image upload support (via [Multer](https://github.com/expressjs/multer))
- ğŸ“¡ Fully accessible from any device on your Wi-Fi network

---

## ğŸ“‹ Requirements

Before running the project, make sure you have the following installed:

| Tool | Version | Description |
|-------|----------|-------------|
| [Node.js](https://nodejs.org/) | v18+ | JavaScript runtime |
| [npm](https://www.npmjs.com/) | v9+ | Node package manager |
| [MongoDB Community Edition](https://www.mongodb.com/try/download/community) | v6+ | Local database server |
| [Git](https://git-scm.com/) | Latest | Version control |

